{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-post-template-tsx","path":"/posts/fireftp-add-on-for-firefox/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"c9ad50cd-cbdb-59f0-912f-f0c113f88254","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/4b190/fireftp.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/8ac56/fireftp.webp 240w,\n/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/d3be9/fireftp.webp 480w,\n/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/d00b9/fireftp.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/09b79/fireftp.jpg 240w,\n/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/7cc5e/fireftp.jpg 480w,\n/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/4b190/fireftp.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/4b190/fireftp.jpg\"\n            alt=\"fireftp\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>FireFTP</strong> is a powerful add-on for Firefox to support FTP. It’s a free, secure, cross-platform FTP/SFTP client for Mozilla Firefox which provides easy and intuitive access to FTP/SFTP servers. It’s a GUI-based FTP client that could be fetched with the lowest cost. It has several advantages:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>As a plugin, it only affects Firefox, which is similar to Chrome’s sandbox.</li>\n<li>As a plugin, it supports multiple character sets, especially GBK, so that Chinese FTP servers that do not use Unicode (UTF-8) can also be easily connected.</li>\n<li>It’s GUI-based, at least it is not as depressing as using the ftp.exe provided by Windows.</li>\n</ol>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/2009-08-25---FireFTP-Add-on-for-Firefox//posts/fireftp-add-on-for-firefox","tagSlugs":["/tag/application/","/tag/firefox/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2009-08-25T20:00:00.000Z","description":"a powerful add-on for Firefox to support FTP.","tags":["Application","Firefox"],"title":"FireFTP Add-on for Firefox","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/1cfb2696f70e37711a9253b420a1930e/fireftp.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2009-08-25---FireFTP-Add-on-for-Firefox//posts/fireftp-add-on-for-firefox"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","288581551","401334301"],"slicesMap":{}}